Marathon Asset Management, LP: Private Company Information - Bloomberg









































  





















































































July 22, 2017 3:27 AM ET
Capital Markets

Company Overview of Marathon Asset Management, LP



Snapshot People




Company Overview
Marathon Asset Management, LP is an investment manager focused on the global credit markets. The firm manages a family of investment programs principally focused on credit strategies including hedge funds, managed accounts, single-client funds, collateralized loan and debt obligation vehicles. It also manages hedge funds, and the Legacy Securities Public Private Investment Program (PPIP) Fund for its clients. The firm manages accounts for banking or thrift institutions, pension and profit sharing plans, pooled investment vehicles, corporations, state or municipal government entities, and university endowment.  It invests in the fixed income markets across the globe. In the corporate credit m...
Marathon Asset Management, LP is an investment manager focused on the global credit markets. The firm manages a family of investment programs principally focused on credit strategies including hedge funds, managed accounts, single-client funds, collateralized loan and debt obligation vehicles. It also manages hedge funds, and the Legacy Securities Public Private Investment Program (PPIP) Fund for its clients. The firm manages accounts for banking or thrift institutions, pension and profit sharing plans, pooled investment vehicles, corporations, state or municipal government entities, and university endowment.  It invests in the fixed income markets across the globe. In the corporate credit market, the firm focuses on distressed and situational non-investment grade opportunities including mispriced capital structures, corporate events in debt, dislocation and mispriced high-yield bonds and leveraged loans, stressed and deeply distressed situations, global approach in high-yield corporate securities, and credit shorts. In the structured credit market, it invests in a wide universe of highly complex distressed, downgraded and non-investment grade structured credit securities including residential mortgage-backed securities, commercial mortgage-backed securities, CDO / CLO, and consumer ABS. The firm employs opportunistic investing and seeks to invest in stressed and deeply distressed situations. It typically employs a fundamental and a technical analysis with a bottom up approach to create its investment portfolio. The firm conducts in-house research to make its investments. Marathon Asset Management, LP was founded in 1998 and is based in New York, New York with additional offices in London, United Kingdom and Singapore.
Detailed Description


